metadata.name: The Frog King
metadata.description:
"The Frog King"
Also known as The Frog Prince, and most popularly The Princess and the Frog.

It is a story about the importance of keeping promises and its rewards.

First published in 1812 by The Brothers Grimm in the first edition of Kinder-und Hausm√§rchen (Children's and Household Tales)

Fact: There was no kissing involved in the original edition.
